Famous Nigerian music artiste, Peter Okoye of the P-Square group has tackled Twitter users who threatened him over his choice of candidate for the forthcoming presidential election. This was contained in a statement via his verified Twitter handle on Friday. The music singer had publicly declared his support for the Labour Party, LP, presidential candidate, Peter Obi. Okoye said the P-square group had become Iconic and legendary and was no longer seeking a career. He wrote, “Stop crying.. We are Global! At this point we will be the one to decide when to retire! We sold out over 70 city World Tour with old songs! Be ready to cry more when our New album drops this summer!. We no longer have a career! We are Iconic and legendary! OG’s before the IG.”